	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64736770"><p>If you are backing into a spot, generally the camera is pretty good, because the act of getting ready to back up has largely taken care of risk of traffic coming at you.</p><p>Problem is lack of peripheral vision, so you really have to look left and right to make sure you aren't backing out in front of someone.  Of course your angle to see that generally sucks anyway, so the cross-traffic alert systems are probably doing a better job of looking around the car you are next to if you do back out (I always back in)</p></div>
