	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64736414"><p>We have a new car, and the biggest problem is storing data in the cloud. Example: each driver has a preferences profile, so you get in, tell it who you are, and the settings are applied. Only: thus sometimes takes *forever*, because the profiles apparently have to be fownlsded from the cloud each time. WTF? That's not much data, surely it should be local?
</p><p>More generally, the car continually uploads its position. Any registered driver can follow the car's movement, which is bad enough, but *who else* has access to that data?</p></div>
	</div>

